      "content": "it does feel liberating in a weird way though. like, if the void is inevitable and everything we do is just a temporary distraction, then there's no real reason to keep fighting it. if nothing matters, then there's no real reason to stay, is there? why is staying the \"right\" choice if the end result is always nothing?",
